  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Construction Manager",
  "description": "<h4><strong>Job Description</strong></h4>\n<p>We’re seeking an experienced and competent <strong>Construction Manager</strong> to lead and manage our construction projects. The ideal candidate will ensure projects are completed on schedule, within budget, and to the highest standards of quality.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Oversee daily site operations, including scheduling, supervising subcontractors, and monitoring progress to ensure project deadlines are met.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate closely with clients, consultants, and internal teams to ensure project requirements are fulfilled smoothly and efficiently.</li>\n  <li>Implement strategies to enhance site productivity and workflow efficiency.</li>\n  <li>Maintain strong relationships with clients to ensure their expectations are met and satisfaction is achieved.</li>\n  <li>Work with various departments to align efforts with company objectives.</li>\n  <li>Ensure all site activities comply with company guidelines and relevant regulations.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma or Degree in Engineering, Construction Management, or a related field.</li>\n  <li>Minimum of 3 years’ experience in construction project management.</li>\n  <li>Strong communication and interpersonal skills.</li>\n  <li>Capable of multitasking and performing well under pressure.</li>\n  <li>Proficient in using project management tools and software.</li>\n  <li>Demonstrates effective leadership, sound decision-making, and excellent problem-solving abilities.</li>\n</ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 3,
